The Director of the White House Office of National Drug Control Policy, Jim Carroll, has released a statement in response to an advisory issued by Surgeon General Vice Adm. Jerome M. Adams. The advisory emphasizes the importance of protecting youth and pregnant women from the health risks of marijuana use. Carroll's statement highlights the increasing scientific evidence of the harmful effects of marijuana use, particularly on young people and pregnant women. The White House is committed to raising awareness about these dangers and is investing in community coalitions to prevent youth substance use. The Surgeon General's advisory can be found in the provided link.